               <msContents>
                  <summary>The author is Philon the baker, who according to the docket writes about payment for work and informs Zenon that he has sent him an artaba and a half of flour.  Other matters were apparently mentioned in the letter, but we have at present only a fragment, the right half and the lower part being still missing.</summary>
